{
  "page": "Merchant's House",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Folko_Streese_Volantis_InnII.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/bb/Folko_Streese_Volantis_InnII.png/350px-Folko_Streese_Volantis_InnII.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"229\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/bb/Folko_Streese_Volantis_InnII.png/525px-Folko_Streese_Volantis_InnII.png 1.5x, /images/b/bb/Folko_Streese_Volantis_InnII.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Folko_Streese_Volantis_InnII.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The interior of the Merchant's House, by Folko Streese © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Merchant's House</b> is the largest inn in <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>. Located on <a href=\"/index.php/Fishermonger%27s_Square_(Volantis)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fishermonger&#39;s Square (Volantis)\">Fishmonger's Square</a> along the western shore of the <a href=\"/index.php/Rhoyne\" title=\"Rhoyne\">Rhoyne</a>, it is popular with foreign travelers<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> and is the first choice for shippers, captains, and merchantmen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Layout\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Layout</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Layout\">Layout</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Merchant%27s_House&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Layout\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dleoblack_Merchant%27s_Widow.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/a/a0/Dleoblack_Merchant%27s_Widow.png/350px-Dleoblack_Merchant%27s_Widow.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"229\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/a/a0/Dleoblack_Merchant%27s_Widow.png/525px-Dleoblack_Merchant%27s_Widow.png 1.5x, /images/a/a0/Dleoblack_Merchant%27s_Widow.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dleoblack_Merchant%27s_Widow.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/index.php/Widow_of_the_waterfront\" title=\"Widow of the waterfront\">widow of the waterfront</a>, by Dleoblack © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The common room is a cavernous warren, larger than the great halls of many <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westerosi</a> castles.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The maze of the common room is built around a central courtyard. A trellis of flowering vines throws intricate patterns across its flagstone floor, and green and purple moss grows between the stones.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The dimly-lit interior of the common room has numerous private alcoves and hidden nooks which are ideal for discrete business. The <a href=\"/index.php/Widow_of_the_waterfront\" title=\"Widow of the waterfront\">widow of the waterfront</a> has a customary table back by the courtyard where she is steeped in shadow. <a href=\"/index.php/Slave\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slave\">Slave</a> girls serve flagons of <a href=\"/index.php/Ale\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ale\">ale</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a>, and an iced green drink that smells of <a href=\"/index.php/Mint\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mint\">mint</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Merchant's House is famous for its locks, which are as secure as a gaol.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> There are cheap rooms on the fourth floor, with iron rings set in the walls for chaining up slaves. One of the rooms, edged into a corner of the building beneath a sloping roof, has a low ceiling, a sagging feather bed with an unpleasant odor, and a slanting wood-plank floor. One window looks toward the <a href=\"/index.php/Long_Bridge\" title=\"Long Bridge\">Long Bridge</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Black_Walls\" title=\"Black Walls\">Black Walls</a>, and the other opens on <a href=\"/index.php/Fishermonger%27s_Square\" title=\"Fishermonger&#39;s Square\">Fishermonger's Square</a> below.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Merchant%27s_House&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>After the death of Triarch <a href=\"/index.php/Vogarro\" title=\"Vogarro\">Vogarro</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Widow_of_the_waterfront\" title=\"Widow of the waterfront\">his widow</a> took up residence at the Merchant's House west and set up her business in its common room.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Merchant%27s_House&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Merchant%27s_House&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Futile_GesturesLukasz_Jaskolski.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/ca/Futile_GesturesLukasz_Jaskolski.jpg/350px-Futile_GesturesLukasz_Jaskolski.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"245\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/ca/Futile_GesturesLukasz_Jaskolski.jpg/525px-Futile_GesturesLukasz_Jaskolski.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/ca/Futile_GesturesLukasz_Jaskolski.jpg/700px-Futile_GesturesLukasz_Jaskolski.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Futile_GesturesLukasz_Jaskolski.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> chained to the wall for the night, by Lukasz Jaskolski © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Martell\" title=\"Quentyn Martell\">Quentyn Martell</a> and his companions, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gerris_Drinkwater\" title=\"Gerris Drinkwater\">Gerris Drinkwater</a> and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Archibald_Yronwood\" title=\"Archibald Yronwood\">Archibald Yronwood</a>, stay at second floor of the Merchant's House while in <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>. The innkeep advises them against traveling by foot, as persons of quality are expected to travel by <a href=\"/index.php/Hathay\" title=\"Hathay\">hathay</a> or <a href=\"/index.php/Palanquin\" title=\"Palanquin\">palanquin</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Prior to leaving for <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a>, four <a href=\"/index.php/Windblown\" title=\"Windblown\">Windblown</a> serjeants set up a trestle table outside of the Merchant's House calling to every passing man and boy, looking for fresh meat to fill their ranks. Their presence hatches Archibald's plan for himself and his companions to join the sellswords as a means to get to <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> and thereby <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jorah_Mormont\" title=\"Jorah Mormont\">Jorah Mormont</a> takes his hostage, <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a>, to the Merchant's House. He chains Tyrion to the wall in a room on the fourth floor and later takes the <a href=\"/index.php/Dwarf\" title=\"Dwarf\">dwarf</a> with him when he meets with the <a href=\"/index.php/Widow_of_the_waterfront\" title=\"Widow of the waterfront\">widow of the waterfront</a> in the common room. Jorah seeks assistance in finding a ship to take himself and Tyrion to Meereen to meet Daenerys. The widow is reluctant to aid them due to Jorah's secretive attitude, but she ultimately offers them the information they need after <a href=\"/index.php/Penny\" title=\"Penny\">Penny</a> attacks Tyrion. The widow has the inn's landlord bring Penny up to her rooms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Merchant%27s_House&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Four stories tall, the Merchant's House dominated the docks and wharves and storehouses that surrounded it. Here traders from <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> mingled with their counterparts from <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentos</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myr</a>, with hairy <a href=\"/index.php/Ibbenese\" title=\"Ibbenese\">Ibbenese</a>, pale-skinned voyagers from <a href=\"/index.php/Qarth\" title=\"Qarth\">Qarth</a>, coal-black <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Islanders\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Summer Islanders\">Summer Islanders</a> in feathered cloaks, even masked <a href=\"/index.php/Shadow-binders\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Shadow-binders\">shadow-binders</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Asshai_by_the_Shadow\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Asshai by the Shadow\">Asshai by the Shadow</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Martell\" title=\"Quentyn Martell\">Quentyn Martell</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Their destination proved to be the Merchant's House, a four-story monstrosity that squatted amongst the warehouses, <a href=\"/index.php/Brothel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brothel\">brothels</a>, and taverns of the waterside like some enormous fat man surrounded by children. Its common room was larger than the great halls of half the castles in <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>, a dim-lit maze of a place with a hundred private alcoves and hidden nooks whose blackened beams and cracked ceilings echoed to the din of sailors, traders, captains, money changers, shippers, and <a href=\"/index.php/Slavers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slavers\">slavers</a>, lying, cursing, and cheating each other in half a hundred different tongues.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Merchant%27s_House&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_6\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 6\">Chapter 6</a>, The Merchant's Man.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\">2.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\">2.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\">2.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\">2.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\">2.6</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-7\">2.7</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-8\">2.8</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_27\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 27\">Chapter 27</a>, Tyrion VII.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403220039\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.056 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.058 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1300/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 9078/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 6037/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1449/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 9/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 3936/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   37